                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/640: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-12T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 12, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. From <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">McCoy</persName>.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“After consultation with <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DNH1"
                            >Davis</persName> and <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1"
                            >Wilson</persName> I am sailing home with <persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_DNH1">Davis</persName> on <hi rend="italic"
                            >Manhattan</hi> on 15th unless I am instructed to the contrary.
                            <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> informs me
                        that there is no probability of the <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1"
                            >Lytton</persName> Commission being recalled by Assembly and we all
                        think as does <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Sir Eric</persName> it
                        would be wiser so. Steps are being taken by <persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> to have Commission
                        formally dissolved as soon as practicable.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
